sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), where a total volume of 30,863 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 3.1 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 68.1% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.5 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $220 strike call option expiring June 28, 2019, with 10,106 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.0 million underlying shares of HD.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $240 strike put option expiring June 14, 2019, with 666 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 66,600 underlying shares of TTD.
